<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title>CheckPoint: Force and Simple Harmonic Motion</title>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <p>
</p><br/> 
Which of the following equations describes simple harmonic motion? <b>Check all that apply.</b>
Note that F, x, v, and a stand for, respectively, force, position, velocity, and acceleration. 
Symbol c is a positive constant.<br/>

    <part loncapaid="20">
      <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="no" loncapaid="15">
        <ul>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=-cv\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=-ca\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=-cx\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=+cx\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=+cv\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=+ca\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil6" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=-x/c\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil7" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=-x^2/c\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil8" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(F=-cv^2\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil9" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </optionresponse>
    </part>
  </problem>
</html>
